From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Date: Fri, 31 Jan 2014 13:47:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] con3270: Use correct name for console driver
References: bnc#861528
Patch-Mainline: not yet

The name for the con3270 driver should be '3270/tty' so that
it can be matched to the actual device entries.

Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>

diff --git a/drivers/s390/char/con3270.c b/drivers/s390/char/con3270.c
index 699fd3e..25a9bff 100644
--- a/drivers/s390/char/con3270.c
+++ b/drivers/s390/char/con3270.c
@@ -564,7 +564,7 @@ static struct notifier_block on_reboot_nb = {
  *  The console structure for the 3270 console
  */
 static struct console con3270 = {
-	.name	 = "tty3270",
+	.name	 = "3270/tty",
 	.write	 = con3270_write,
 	.device	 = con3270_device,
 	.flags	 = CON_PRINTBUFFER,
